        "answer": "C",
        "explanation": "1 whole = 4/4. 2 wholes = 2 × 4 = 8 fourths."
      },
      {
        "id": "PT_05",
        "type": "mc",
        "difficulty": 2,
        "question": "Which whole number is equal to 6/3?",
        "choices": [
          "1",
          "2",
          "3",
          "6"
        ],
        "answer": "B",
        "explanation": "6 ÷ 3 = 2. So 6/3 = 2."
      }
    ],
    "learn": [
      {
        "id": "LRN_01",
        "type": "card",
        "title": "Fractions That Equal 1",
        "content": "When the numerator and denominator are the same, the fraction equals 1 whole. Examples: 2/2 = 1, 3/3 = 1, 4/4 = 1, 8/8 = 1."
      },
      {
        "id": "LRN_02",
        "type": "card",
        "title": "Fractions Greater Than 1",
        "content": "When the numerator is greater than the denominator, the fraction is greater than 1. Example: 8/4 means you have 8 fourths. Since 4 fourths = 1 whole, 8 fourths = 2 wholes. So 8/4 = 2."
      },
      {
        "id": "LRN_03",
        "type": "card",
        "title": "Whole Numbers as Fractions",
        "content": "Any whole number can be written as a fraction. Multiply the whole number by the denominator to find the numerator. Example: 3 = 3 × 4 / 4 = 12/4. Also 3 = 6/2 = 9/3 = 12/4 = 24/8."
      }
    ],
